<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Having seen the highs and lows of pvp in meridian 59, ultima online and everquest, I find myself wondering how daoc will avoid some of the common pitfalls.<P>The first question that comes to mind is what will prevent cross-teaming?  This has been the bane of team pvp in eq.<P>The other issue is with the measures taken to restrict communication in the game.  The positives are that it adds to immersion and atmosphere, in fact it was one of the things I liked a great deal about UO.  The high overhead required to circumvent it (phone line, 2nd computer, roger wilco, etc etc) means that very few players will absorb the cost to do so.  However, the unintended consequence I see here is that the few who do circumvent it can band together to dominate pvp--every time.<P>The fun would quickly fade with such an unlevel playing field.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
