<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I've honestly never been much for PvP. My first experience with it was UO when it first came out, and I was rather annoyed and sometimes disgusted.. I usually see PvP as a bunch of juvenille high schoolers who want to ruin the game for everyone else, EQ didn't improve it much. I had a character on one of the race war servers, and after watching a gnome camping newbies in Greater Faydark, I decided that PvP was exactly what I thought it was in the first place.. Like Junt said though, great comment btw, this will be defending your realm, your home, your people, it adds a little nobility to PvP which I hadn't seen before.. This might be wishful thinking, but I think DAoC will be different..<P>Aridhol<BR>(future elven bard)<P>--------------------<P>Life is like a great play; best accompanied by song.<P>Aridhol<BR>(future elven bard)
